news.title: Land registry to get costlier by up to 20% from today in Bhopal
news.para: According to district administration sources, the registry of land will go up by 5% to 20% at 732 locations in Bhopal from April 1 following revision of collector guidelines rates.

news.title: Both Pune civic body & PCMC set records in property tax collection in 2022-23
news.para: Till Friday, the last day of the financial year, the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) collected Rs 1,963 crore, while the Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) collected Rs 810 crore as property tax.

news.title: At close of fiscal, Chandigarh civic body earns Rs 69.5 crore as property tax
news.para: The property tax amount has been collected from both commercial and residential properties of the city. Some amount has also been received from people in the form of title change of properties and through book entries.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body earns Rs 4 crore in property tax on last payment day
news.para: The officials claimed that the tax was collected at suvidha centres till late evening and online payment was available till midnight. They are expecting the collection to touch Rs 125 crore mark this year.

news.title: Highest ever property tax collected in Nashik at Rs 187 crore
news.para: The target for property tax collection this fiscal was Rs 185 crore. The civic body has collected Rs187 crore, as per the data provided by the property tax department.

news.title: PE firm exits Shriram Properties; sells entire stake for Rs 134 crore
news.para: The entire stake was acquired by Aurum Realestate Developers, as per the block deal data available on the National Stock Exchange (NSE).

news.title: Zara founder buys luxury apartment building in Dublin for $108 million
news.para: It is the first residential building that Ortega's firm has bought outside the United States, Pontegadea said, adding it was part of its strategy to invest in multiple real estate assets.

news.title: No illegal buildings in Faridabad Aravalis razed despite SC order
news.para: The government sought a four-month extension for the exercise, which expired in February. Three committees were set up and notices issued to the encroachers in October last year, but the demolitions are yet to be carried out.

news.title: Over Rs 5,300 crore recovered by BMC in property tax by end of FY23
news.para: Significantly, the BMC had initially announced a tax target of Rs 6,000 crore for the fiscal 2022-23, which it revised to 4,800 crore earlier this year. The civic body's total collection for the previous fiscal stood at Rs 5,792 crore.

news.title: ED attaches property worth Rs 83 crore of Kalptaru Buildtech
news.para: These properties are in Lucknow, Agra, Mathura, Aligarh and others. A case of Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002 (PMLA) was registered against the firm in March 2022.

news.title: Singapore government sells 2.9% stake in Phoenix Mills for Rs 670 crore
news.para: In a bulk deal data transaction on NSE, the Singapore government offloaded more than 51.49 lakh shares, amounting to a 2.88 per cent stake in the firm.

news.title: Maharashtra government decides not to hike ready reckoner rates for FY24
news.para: The Ready Reckoner rates are guidance values for property transactions in a specific locality and are used for calculation of stamp duty charges and taxes. The development charges and other premiums paid by the builders to civic bodies are also determined based on these rates.

news.title: Noida: Sunworld Residence's three under-construction towers sealed over unpaid dues
news.para: Officer on Special Duty (Group Housing) Prasun Dwivedi said notices were issued to real estate developer Sunworld Residence Private Limited in November and December 2022 regarding payment of dues, which remain to be cleared to date.

news.title: Trichy may get Tidel park as officials scout for sites
news.para: Tidel is a joint venture of Tamil Nadu Industrial Development Corporation (Tidco) and Electronic Corporation of Tamil Nadu (Elcot).

news.title: Sunac China working to secure funding to complete projects, chairman says
news.para: Sunac has introduced distressed asset managers (AMC) into 20 billion yuan ($2.91 billion) worth of major projects, and implemented 11 billion yuan of loans from the government special fund, he said.
